            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@FUZxxl:  It&apos;s true the VMS used odd values (like 1) to indicate success and even values (like 0) to indicate failure.  Unfortunately, the original ANSI C standard was interpreted to mean that EXIT_SUCCESS had to be 0, so returning EXIT_SUCCESS from main got exactly the wrong behavior on VMS.  The portable thing to do for VMS was to use &lt;code&gt;exit(EXIT_SUCCESS)&lt;/code&gt;, which always did the right thing.&lt;/span&gt;

